'''William "Billy" Levy''' is an American entrepreneur best known for co-founding the eSports platform, ''[[Virgin Gaming]]'', with [[Sir Richard Branson]] and Zack Zeldin.<ref name=Vibe>June 15, 2010. "Virgin Group Takes Chance on Game Site" [https://www.nytimes.com/2010/06/15/technology/15game.html]. Eric A. Taub. ''The New York Times''.</ref>

A serial entrepreneur, Levy has co-founded on demand tech support business, ''Nerd Alert'', federally licensed Canadian medical cannabis business, ''Agripharm Corp.'' (acquired by ''Mettrum''), and mobile commerce platform, ''Virgin Mega'' (acquired by ''[[Nike, Inc.|Nike]]'').<ref name=SS>April 1, 2015. "Nerd Alert offers on-demand tech support" [http://www.sun-sentinel.com/local/palm-beach/boynton-beach/fl-bbf-nerd-0401-20150401-story.html] Jan Engoren. ''Sun Sentinel''.</ref><ref name=Agripharm>September 9, 2015. “A Visit to Mettrum’s Agripharm facility” [https://news.lift.co/a-visit-to-mettrums-agripharm-facility/]. David Brown. ''Lift News''.</ref><ref name=VM>August 3, 2016. “Nike Acquires Virgin Mega to Improve the Way We Buy Sneakers” [https://hypebeast.com/2016/8/nike-acquires-virgin-mega-to-possibly-combat-bots] Ben Roazen. ''HYPEBEAST''.</ref>

