{{multiple issues| {{BLP sources|date=November 2017}} {{tone|date=November 2017}} }} Rabbi '''Chaim Dovid Zweibel''' is the Executive Vice-President of [[Agudath Israel of America]].<ref>"The Jewish Community Council of Marine Park (JCCMP) hosted Rabbi Chaim Dovid Zwiebel, Executive Vice President ...{{cite web |title=JCC of Marine Park Hosts Rabbi Chaim Dovid Zweibel For ... |url=https://www.theyeshivaworld.com/news/interesting-news-alerts/58303/jcc-of-marine-park-hosts-rabbi-chaim-dovid-zweibel-for-inspirational-shabbos.html |date=May 23, 2010}}</ref><ref>"He later met with community organizational leaders, including Rabbi Chaim Dovid Zweibel, Executive VP of Agudath Israel of America"{{cite web |title=Trump Advisor Meets FJCC Leadership In Flatbush |url=http://jewishvoiceny.com/index.php?option=com_content%26view=article%26id=14658:trump-advisor-meets-fjcc-leadership-in-flatbush%26catid=112:new-york%26Itemid=295 |date=June 1, 2016| website=JewishVoiceNY.com}}</ref> Rabbi Zweibel joined the organization as a vice president <ref name=Join.2001>{{cite web |url=http://www.chareidi.org/archives5761/yisro/azwiebel.htm |title=Agudas Yisroel Vice President Rabbi Chaim Dovid Zweibel: The Struggle for Equality is a Real Problem |author=Yisroel Friedman |date=February 14, 2001 |website=chareidi.org}}</ref> after working for 30 years at a law firm,<ref name=FWD.50>{{cite newspaper |newspaper=The Forward |url=http://forward.com/series/forward-50/2012/david-zwiebel |title=David Zwiebel |date=2012}}</ref> and was selected for his current position in 2008 after the passing of his predecessor, Rabbi [[Moshe Sherer]].<ref name=Fwd>{{cite newspaper |newspaper=The Forward |title=David Zweibel, Agudath Israel of America – Salary Survey 2015 |url=http://forward.com/series/salary-survey/2015/david-zweibel/agudath-israel-of-america}}</ref>
==Prior involvement== Zweibel was part of the 1992 effort by "conservative Catholic and Jewish groups,"<ref>{{cite newspaper |newspaper=The New York Times |date=May 12, 1992 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/1992/05/12/us/new-york-rule-compounds-dilemma-over-life-support.html |title=New York Rule Compounds Dilemma Over Life Support |author=LISA BELKIN}}</ref> to oppose "right-to-die" proponents who were advocating for legislation to "allow family members to speak for patients who can no longer speak for themselves." At that time, he was serving Aguda as general counsel and director of government affairs.
==As Executive Vice President== He helped Agudath Israel organize and operate the August 2012 National Celebration of the 12th [[Siyum HaShas]] in [[MetLife Stadium]], the largest gathering for [[Orthodox Jew]]ry in the history of the United States; 90,000 people attended.<ref name=FWD.50/>
As part of an ongoing<ref>"New York City’s health commissioner and Agudath Israel respond to an editorial" {{cite newspaper |newspaper=The New York Times |date=March 11, 2015 |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/03/11/opinion/orthodox-jews-and-new-yorks-circumcision-rule.html |title=Orthodox Jews and New York’s Circumcision Rule}}</ref> challenge regarding religious freedom, Zweibel, described by The New York Times as "leader of an ultra-Orthodox group,"<ref>"with community leaders, including leaders of Agudath Israel of America, Rabbi Chaim Dovid Zweibel, Sol Werdiger, and Chaskel Bennett." {{cite web |title=Trump's Israel advisor visits Brooklyn Jewish community |url=http://jewishjournal.com/news/nation/185822 |website=JewishJournal.com |date=May 26, 2016}}</ref> was successful in pushing for the repeal by current NYC Mayor de Blasio<ref>{{cite newspaper |newspaper=The New York Times |date=February 25, 2015 |author=MICHAEL M. GRYNBAUM |title=De Blasio Set to Waive Rule Requiring Consent Form for Circumcision Ritual |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2015/02/25/nyregion/de-blasio-set-to-waive-rule-requiring-consent-form-for-circumcision-ritual.html}}</ref> of what The Times had previously called prior Mayor Bloomberg's attempt "to regulate Jewish Circumcision."<ref>{{cite web |website=NYTimes.com |url=https://www.nytimes.com/2012/09/14/nyregion/health-board-votes-to-regulate-jewish-circumcision-ritual.html |title=Health Board Votes To Regulate Jewish Circumcision Ritual}}</ref>
